==Yearly Offerings ==
* History of Items-of-the-Year: 
**From Mr. Store's founding in 2004 until 2011, Mr. Store had two familiars for sale at the cost of two {{plural|Mr. Accessory}}. One of them increased item drops like a [[Baby Gravy Fairy]] and increased meat drops like a [[Leprechaun]], and the other increased stat gains from combat like a [[Blood-Faced Volleyball]] and increased meat drops like a [[Leprechaun]]. These familiars were available for one year, from early October one year until early October the next year.
**Beginning in January 2012, the familiars began rotating at the start of the year, and through 2015 they each had a new ability: the Fairy/Leprechaun also dropped items which [[Content Familiar|unlocked additional content]], and the Volleyball/Leprechaun dropped consumables which gave adventures for [[spleen]].
**Beginning in January 2016, Mr. Store replaced the Fairy/Leprechaun and Volleyball/Leprechaun with a single familiar that increases stat gains from combat like a [[Blood-Faced Volleyball]] and increases item drops like a [[Baby Gravy Fairy]]. It also drops consumables, but they neither unlock new content nor give adventures for [[spleen]]. In 2016, a separately purchased consumable unlocked additional content; no new annual content was available in 2017, 2018, nor 2019. Some of Mr. Store's monthly items continue to [[:Category:Content Unlockers|unlock additional content]], however.  In 2018, the annual familiar was one that also increases item drops like a [[Baby Gravy Fairy]], but restores HP and MP like a [[Ghuol Whelp]] instead of increasing stat gains. 
**Beginning in January 2020, Mr. Store replaced the familiar offering with an item offering. The price was also lowered from two {{plural|Mr. Accessory}} to one.
**In January 2025, Mr. Store had the item offering act as a [[:Category:Content Unlockers|content unlocker]], but the price was reraised to two {{plural|Mr. Accessory}}. However, 2026 saw the return of the 2020-2024 ''status quo ante''. 

