==Notes==
*Players making donations through a [[Options#Account|subscription]] may choose to receive the Item of the Month directly, which will be kmailed to them by SubscriptionBot, usually about a day before it is released into Mr. Store.
*While in [[Hardcore]], players who have one or more {{plural|Mr. Accessory}} in [[Hagnk's Ancestral Mini-Storage]] may pull them out of storage in order to spend them in Mr. Store. They can not be equipped in Hardcore. If they drop Hardcore that day, they will find that these pulls have counted against their 20-pull limit.
*While in Hardcore, players can place Mr. Store familiars into their [[Familiar-Gro™ Terrarium (Campground)|Familiar-Gro™ Terrarium]], put books into their Mystical Bookshelf, and use most other IotMs that are available or auto-pulled at the start of a run.  However, trying to equip an IotM in Hardcore that isn't auto-pulled for the path you're on (for example, choosing Zombie Slayer, dropping the path and trying to equip the bear arms) will return the following instead:
*:You can't equip your <item name> while in Hardcore mode.
*In a [[Zombie Slayer]] run, Mr. Shopkeeper has changed (but the store is still open):
{| style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"
|-
| [[File:mrkeeper_z.gif]]
| Braaaaains. Traaaade. Mr. Graaaaagh.
|}
